# Cloud Journey - Day 11

## Topic Learned

* AWS Certificate Manager (ACM)

## What is ACM?

AWS Certificate Manager (ACM) is a service used to provision, manage, and automatically renew SSL/TLS certificates for AWS resources.

ACM helps secure websites and applications by enabling HTTPS communication.

---

## Why ACM is Needed

Without HTTPS:

```text
User
 ↓
HTTP
 ↓
Website
```

Data is transferred in plain text.

With ACM:

```text
User
 ↓
HTTPS
 ↓
ACM Certificate
 ↓
Website
```

Data is encrypted and transmitted securely.

---

## Key Concepts

### SSL/TLS Certificates

* Used to enable HTTPS.
* Encrypt communication between clients and servers.
* Verify the identity of a website.

### Domain Validation

Before issuing a certificate, ACM verifies ownership of the domain using:

* DNS Validation (recommended)
* Email Validation

### Automatic Renewal

ACM automatically renews eligible certificates before expiration.

---

## AWS Services Integrated with ACM

* Application Load Balancer (ALB)
* CloudFront
* API Gateway
* Elastic Beanstalk

---

## Common Architecture

```text
User
 ↓
Route 53
 ↓
ALB + ACM Certificate
 ↓
EC2
```

Route 53 resolves the domain, ACM provides the SSL/TLS certificate, and ALB serves HTTPS traffic securely.

---

## Benefits of ACM

* Free public SSL/TLS certificates
* Automatic certificate renewal
* Easy integration with AWS services
* Improved security
* Enables HTTPS communication

---

## ACM vs Route 53

| ACM                          | Route 53              |
| ---------------------------- | --------------------- |
| Manages SSL/TLS certificates | Manages DNS records   |
| Enables HTTPS                | Routes traffic        |
| Provides encryption          | Resolves domain names |

---

## ACM vs KMS

| ACM                          | KMS                      |
| ---------------------------- | ------------------------ |
| Manages SSL/TLS certificates | Manages encryption keys  |
| Used for HTTPS security      | Used for data encryption |
| Secures communication        | Secures stored data      |

---

## Interview Questions

### What is AWS ACM?

AWS Certificate Manager (ACM) is a service that provisions, manages, and automatically renews SSL/TLS certificates used to secure AWS applications and websites.

### Why use ACM?

To enable HTTPS, encrypt data in transit, verify domain ownership, and simplify certificate management.

### Which AWS services commonly use ACM?

ALB, CloudFront, API Gateway, and Elastic Beanstalk.

---

## Key Takeaway

ACM simplifies SSL/TLS certificate management in AWS by providing free certificates, automatic renewal, and seamless integration with AWS services to secure applications using HTTP


